{"pageProps":{"eyebrow":"AgentSight","page":{"layout":"document","title":"AgentSight npm package","description":"AgentSight publishes @eunomia-bpf/agentsight as the official npm entrypoint for the Web viewer and command dispatcher.","descriptionIsExcerpt":true,"bodyHtml":"<p>AgentSight publishes <code>@eunomia-bpf/agentsight</code> as the official npm entrypoint\nfor the Web viewer and command dispatcher.</p>\n<p>The npm <code>agentsight</code> command has two responsibilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>agentsight web</code>, <code>agentsight serve</code>, and <code>agentsight open</code> serve the bundled\nWeb UI for exported snapshots.</li>\n<li><code>agentsight record</code>, <code>agentsight top</code>, <code>agentsight monitor</code>,\n<code>agentsight stat</code>, and <code>agentsight report</code> delegate to a real Rust AgentSight\ncollector binary when one is available.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The npm package does not run privileged commands, download hidden binaries, or\nexecute a <code>postinstall</code> installer.</p>\n<h2 id=\"build-locally\">Build locally</h2>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">npm</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ci</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> --prefix</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> frontend</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">node</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> frontend/scripts/prepare-sample.mjs</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">npm</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> run</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> build</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> --prefix</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> frontend</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">node</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> script/npm/sync-version.mjs</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">node</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> script/npm/prepare-agentsight.mjs</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h2 id=\"validate-locally\">Validate locally</h2>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">cd</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> package/npm/agentsight</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">npm</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> test</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">npm</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> pack</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> --dry-run</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h2 id=\"publish\">Publish</h2>\n<p>Publishing is handled by <code>.github/workflows/npm-publish.yml</code> on\n<code>workflow_dispatch</code>, GitHub Release publish, or <code>v*</code> tag push. The workflow uses\nnpm Trusted Publishing with GitHub Actions OIDC and skips versions that already\nexist.</p>\n<p>Configure npm Trusted Publishing for:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Package: <code>@eunomia-bpf/agentsight</code></li>\n<li>Publisher: GitHub Actions</li>\n<li>GitHub organization/user: <code>eunomia-bpf</code></li>\n<li>Repository: <code>agentsight</code></li>\n<li>Workflow filename: <code>npm-publish.yml</code></li>\n<li>Allowed action: <code>npm publish</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Manual local publishing is equivalent to:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">cd</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> package/npm/agentsight</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">npm</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> publish</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> --access</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> public</span></span></code></pre></figure>","tags":[],"headings":[{"id":"build-locally","text":"Build locally","depth":2},{"id":"validate-locally","text":"Validate locally","depth":2},{"id":"publish","text":"Publish","depth":2}],"sourcePath":"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia.dev/tree/main/docs/agentsight/npm.md","metadata":{"updatedAt":"2026-07-15T23:10:39.000Z","createdAt":"2026-07-15T23:10:39.000Z","authors":[{"name":"github-actions[bot]","email":"41898282+github-actions[bot]@users.noreply.github.com"}]},"path":"/agentsight/npm/","alternates":{"en":"/agentsight/npm/","zh":"/zh/agentsight/npm/"},"continuation":{"index":{"title":"AgentSight: System-wide AI agent profiling and monitoring with eBPF","description":"![License: MIT](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT) ![CI](https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/agentsight/actions/workflows/ci.yml) ![arXiv:2508.02736](https://arxiv.org/abs/2508.02736)","href":"/agentsight/"},"previous":{"title":"AgentSight: System-wide AI agent profiling and monitoring with eBPF","description":"![License: MIT](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT) ![CI](https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/agentsight/actions/workflows/ci.yml) ![arXiv:2508.02736](https://arxiv.org/abs/2508.02736)","href":"/agentsight/"},"next":{"title":"OpenTelemetry GenAI Export","description":"AgentSight can export the LLM calls it captures as OpenTelemetry GenAI semantic-convention (genai.) spans, sent to any OpenTelemetry Collector over OTLP/HTTP.","href":"/agentsight/otel/"}},"sidebar":[{"title":"AgentSight","items":[{"title":"Overview","href":"/agentsight/"},{"title":"Quick start","href":"/agentsight/usage/"},{"title":"Supported agents","href":"/agentsight/agents/"},{"title":"Build from source","href":"/agentsight/build/"},{"title":"Docker","href":"/agentsight/docker/"},{"title":"OpenTelemetry","href":"/agentsight/otel/"},{"title":"agentpprof","href":"/agentsight/agentpprof/"},{"title":"Development","href":"/agentsight/development/"}]}]}},"__N_SSG":true}